The core vulnerability is that Retrofit's @Url annotation accepts any URL/path string and resolves it against the base URL with no domain or path prefix validation, enabling SSRF (absolute URL override) and path escaping (via ../ sequences). For @Path with encoded=true, the canonicalization does not sanitize dot-dot sequences.
